    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "attributesToDisplay is meant to be an array of strings, I wonder if what you're looking for is a separate data-bag to store these more \"static\" information. Would that help your use case?\r\n\r\nSomething along the lines of:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  // ... other configuration\r\n  \"attributesToDisplay\": [],\r\n  \"data\": {\r\n    \"hit\": {\r\n      \"title\": {\r\n        \"href\": \"url\",\r\n        \"text\": \"hierarchy.lvl2\",\r\n        \"highlight\": true\r\n      },\r\n      \"subtitle\": {\r\n        \"text\": \"hierarchy.lvl1\"\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf you're interested in that, we'd be happy to see a PR adding a new `data` field from config that's copied over to the template variables.\r\n",
