    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I see your use case, but `attributesForFaceting` also doesn't tolerate non-array shapes, it in fact completely ignores the value and will put `false` if you put anything but an array of strings. I'm still happy to approve a purpose-built feature though. You're right that attributesForFaceting and attributesToDisplay are inconsistent, so I'll make a fix to reject non-arrays in both in the same way.",
